=== chime_dm manifest ===
{
  "generated_by": "analysis/chime_dm/plot_dm_grid.py (data: scripts/dump_grid_data.py, baseband docker)",
  "manuscript_order": 20,
  "regen": "python analysis/chime_dm/plot_dm_grid.py",
  "figures": [
    {
      "path": "chime_dm_grid.png",
      "expectation": "12-panel grid (4 cols x 3 rows), one cell per co-detected burst, ordered 8 constrained then 4 non-detections. Each cell: (top) coherent-dedispersed-at-DSA-DM waterfall nu[MHz] vs t[ms], magma z-score, with a ~1 ms (12-bin) boxcar time-smoothing applied for DISPLAY ONLY (does not touch the DM regression); (bottom) scatter-deconvolved sub-band arrival t0[ms] vs K_DM(nu^-2 - nu_ref^-2)[s] with a red weighted-linear fit whose slope is the residual DM offset. EXPECT: the 8 constrained bursts (zach, casey, freya, hamilton, chromatica, isha, wilhelm, phineas; titles green) show a visible dispersed burst in the waterfall and a regression with green points + red fit line annotated dDM and sigma; their slope is NEAR-FLAT (residual DM ~ 0 -> de-biased to DSA, |dDM| <= 0.84, all within the 1 pc/cm^3 floor). The 4 non-detections (whitney, oran, johndoeII, mahi; titles grey, DM='--') show a noise-dominated waterfall and a 'non-detection (n<3 sub-bands)' box instead of a fit. Confirm: no constrained panel has a steep positive slope (would be the old +2-3 S/N-max scattering bias); annotated dDM matches the visual slope sign; non-det panels genuinely lack a burst; axes ~400-800 MHz, sane ms ranges, no empty constrained panels."
    }
  ],
  "result": {
    "config": "coherent_dedisp at DSA DM; uniform TDS=32 / N_SB=6; MIN_SNR=4; MIN_GOOD=3 sub-bands; 1 pc/cm^3 agreement floor",
    "constrained_8": {"zach": -0.84, "casey": -0.04, "freya": -0.12, "hamilton": 0.04, "chromatica": -0.28, "isha": -0.35, "wilhelm": -0.44, "phineas": -0.45},
    "non_detections_4": ["whitney", "oran", "johndoeII", "mahi"],
    "note": "dDM = DM_CHIME - DM_DSA [pc/cm^3]; statistical sigma is a lower bound for the 3-4 sub-band fits, the floor governs the consistency test."
  }
}
=== chime_dm review ===
{
  "reviewed_by": "claude-opus-4-8 (figure-review gate, read chime_dm_grid.png @ TSMOOTH=12)",
  "date": "2026-06-24",
  "verdicts": [
    {
      "path": "chime_dm_grid.png",
      "verdict": "match",
      "notes": "12-panel grid with ~1 ms (12-bin) display-only boxcar time-smoothing on the waterfalls (DM regression untouched). TOP 8 (green, constrained): zach/casey/freya/hamilton are crisp bright vertical burst streaks; the faint rescued chromatica/isha/wilhelm/phineas now stand cleanly out of the speckle -- markedly more legible than the unsmoothed render. All 8 regression panels carry green sub-band points + a near-flat red fit, annotated dDM in [-0.84,+0.04] and sigma/n matching chime_dm_grid_fits.json; no steep positive (S/N-max-bias) slope anywhere. BOTTOM 4 (grey, DM='--'): whitney/mahi are noise; oran/johndoeII show smoothing-enhanced sub-threshold diagonal structure (n=1-2 sub-bands, below the >=3 gate) but correctly carry the 'non-detection (n<3 sub-bands)' box and NO fit -- honest, the label prevents misreading them as detections. Smoothing chosen as the s6/s12/s20 sweet spot: s20 over-emphasized the non-det artifacts. Axes 400.4-799.2 MHz, ms ranges sane, no empty constrained panels. Scientifically faithful to the 8/12 result."
    }
  ]
}
